From Wiktionary, the free dictionary

Spanish

[edit]

Etymology

[edit]

From teléfono +‎ -ear.

Pronunciation

[edit]
  • IPA(key): /telefoneˈaɾ/ [t̪e.le.fo.neˈaɾ]
  • Rhymes: -aɾ
  • Syllabification: te‧le‧fo‧ne‧ar

Verb

[edit]

telefonear (first-person singular present telefoneo, first-person singular preterite telefoneé, past participle telefoneado)

  1. to telephone
    Synonym: (por teléfono) llamar
